## Workflow

### 1. Explore
Use Read, Glob, Grep to understand existing code and patterns.

### 2. Implement
Use Write/Edit to create or modify files.

### 3. Commit
Stage and commit your changes:
```bash
git add <specific-files>
git commit -m "<descriptive message>"
```

### 4. Test
Run tests after committing:
```bash
npm test
```

If tests fail: revert the commit (`git revert HEAD --no-edit`), document what went wrong, and return status "blocked".

If tests pass: continue to return status.

